Nestle South Africa has confirmed it will stop producing Chocolate Log from August. JOHANNESBURG - Some sad news for chocoholics. Nestlé South Africa has confirmed it will stop producing Chocolate Log from August. READ: Chokoloza in world's biggest chocolate show Lovers of the marshmallow-wafer delight took to social media to express their dismay. The Chocolate Log has been around for 50-years. In a statement, Nestlé thanked its loyal customers for their support over the years and assured them a variety of delicious chocolates will be launched in the coming months.